						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine of the Tiruvandanathēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Vikramachōḷa.</p>						

						<p>The date is lost in the damaged portion of the inscription. This inscription records a gift of 17 sheep () by one Nārāyaṇa <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Nāṟpatteṇṇāyirakkōṉ of a village in Kaḷattūrkōṭṭam in Jayaṅgoṇḍaśōḻa-maṇḍalam towards part of the cost of burning a perpetual lamp.</p>						

						</summary>
